<paragraph blockId="11.[813,1452,1560,1968]" lastBlockId="12.[136,775,1463,1583]" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="13" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
The skeletal anatomy of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1876" baseAuthorityName="Hilton" baseAuthorityYear="2003" box="[1129,1233,1688,1712]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pantodontidae" genus="Pantodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Osteoglossiformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1129,1233,1688,1712]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Pantodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been described and illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Taverne" box="[1013,1181,1720,1744]" firstAuthor="Taverne" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="1 - 213" refId="ref27979" refString="Taverne L. Osteologie, phylogenese, et systematique des teleosteens fossiles et actuels du super-ordre des osteoglossomorphes, deuxieme partie. Osteologie des genres Phareodus, Phareoides, Brychaetus, Musperia, Pantodon, Singida, Notopterus, Xenomystus et Papyrocranus. Acad Roy Belg Mem Cl Sci. 1978; 42 (6): 1 - 213. (Collection 8, Serie 2)." type="journal article" year="1978">Taverne (1978)</bibRefCitation>
, and portions of its skeleton was illustrated and described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hilton" box="[1251,1402,1752,1776]" firstAuthor="Hilton" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="1 - 100" refId="ref22345" refString="Hilton EJ. Comparative osteology and phylogenetic systematics of fossil and living bony-tongue fishes (Actinopterygii, Teleostei, Osteoglossomorpha). Zool J Linn Soc [serial on the Internet]. 2003; 137 (1): 1 - 100. Available from: https: // doi. org / 10.1046 / j. 1096 - 3642.2003.00032. x" type="journal article" year="2003">Hilton (2003)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Hilton, Britz" box="[813,1031,1784,1808]" firstAuthor="Hilton" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="219 - 237" refId="ref22408" refString="Hilton EJ, Britz R. The caudal skeleton of osteoglossomorph fishes, revisited: comparisons, homologies, and characters. In: Nelson JS, Schultze H-P, Wilson MVH, editors. Origin and phylogenetic interrelationships of teleosts. Munchen: Verlag Dr. Friedrich Pfeil; 2010. p. 219 - 237." type="book chapter" year="2010">Hilton, Britz (2010)</bibRefCitation>
. In a study of its development, 
<bibRefCitation author="Moritz, Britz" firstAuthor="Moritz" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="1 - 13" refId="ref25164" refString="Moritz T, Britz R. Ontogeny and homology of the basipterygoid articulation in Pantodon buchholzi (Teleostei: Osteoglossomorpha). Zool J Lin Soc [serial on the Internet]. 2005; 144: 1 - 13. Available from: https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.2005.00163. x" type="journal article" year="2005">Moritz, Britz (2005)</bibRefCitation>
showed that the single dermal bone of the palatoquadrate in the adult of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1876" baseAuthorityName="Hilton" baseAuthorityYear="2003" box="[1087,1191,1848,1872]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pantodontidae" genus="Pantodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Osteoglossiformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1087,1191,1848,1872]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Pantodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an ontogenetic fusion of the dermopalatine and ectopterygoid. They further conclude that the basipterygoid articulation found in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1876" baseAuthorityName="Hilton" baseAuthorityYear="2003" box="[1348,1452,1912,1936]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pantodontidae" genus="Pantodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Osteoglossiformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1348,1452,1912,1936]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Pantodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bonaparte" authorityYear="1831" baseAuthorityName="Moritz, Britz" baseAuthorityYear="2005" box="[857,1018,1944,1968]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Osteoglossidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Osteoglossiformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Osteoglossidae</taxonomicName>
is structurally homologous to that found in non-teleosts and a basal clupeomorph, and therefore is a character at a broader level of phylogeny than uniting a subgroup of osteoglossomorphs (
<emphasis box="[458,490,1528,1551]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">e.g</emphasis>
., 
<bibRefCitation author="Greenwood" box="[512,771,1527,1551]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Greenwood" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="339 - 456" refId="ref21932" refString="Greenwood PH, Rosen DE, Weitzman SH, Myers GS. Phyletic studies of teleostean fishes, with a provisional classification of living forms. Bull Am Mus Nat Hist. 1966; 131 (4): 339 - 456." type="journal article" year="1966">
Greenwood 
<emphasis box="[644,700,1527,1551]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">et al.</emphasis>
, 1966
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Lauder, Liem" box="[136,349,1559,1583]" firstAuthor="Lauder" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="95 - 197" refId="ref23618" refString="Lauder GV, Liem KF. The evolution and interrelationships of the actinopterygian fishes. Bull Mus Comp Zool. 1983; 150 (3): 95 - 197." type="journal article" year="1983">Lauder, Liem, 1983</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Arratia, Schultze" box="[359,610,1559,1583]" firstAuthor="Arratia" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="1 - 81" refId="ref18812" refString="Arratia G, Schultze H-P. Palatoquadrate and its ossifications: Development and homology within osteichthyans. J Morphol [serial on the Internet]. 1991; 208 (1): 1 - 81. Available from: https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / jmor. 1052080102" type="journal article" year="1991">Arratia, Schultze, 1991</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
